HEADWORD: Sapor
<hw>Sa"por</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. See
<er>Savor</er>.]</ety> <def>Power of affecting the organs of taste;
savor; flavor; taste.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is some <qex>sapor</qex> in all aliments.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saporific</ent>⟦br⟧
